---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>hungovercoders</h1>
			<p>
				I wanted a single place on the internet that was mine. Source-controlled, cheap to run,
				honest about how it works. The kind of tech blog you'd write if you didn't have to impress
				anyone — just help a fellow hungovercoder get something working before the next round.
			</p>
			<p>This is it.</p>
			<p>
				The posts are walkthroughs of things I actually built — data pipelines, cloud infrastructure,
				APIs, DevOps tooling. Not theoretical. Not sanitised. Sometimes written on a Friday. The code
				ran on my laptop first.
			</p>
			<p>
				The worldview, if you want it in one sentence: <strong>small, cheap, and yours beats big,
				fancy, and rented.</strong> If one slightly hungover person can't deploy it on a Tuesday,
				it's too complicated.
			</p>
			<p>
				<a href="/blog">Read the blog</a> or <a href="/about">find out who's behind it</a>.
				Read on, fellow hungovercoder.
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
